You are wrong Miriadi. You do not understand how pet aggro work. If any PC is in melee range the mob will switch to that PC wether or not the charmed pet is actually higher on the hate list than the PC. It's kinda similar to how root aggro work. If the PC step out of range, the mob will not follow.<P>And buffing or complete healing a pet is minimal aggro, just enough to put you at the bottom of the hate list. Try it out, send a mage pet against 4-5 critters at the same time and you can complete heal him all day and they will stay stuck on the pet.
