<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Saltino, making personal attacks does not help validate your argument in anyway.  <P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>And btw mr illusionist (wich means nothing to us here)<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>this was the title given to the winners of the botb.  it may not mean anything to you, but it does to alot of people.<P>before you do a list of top 10 reasons something is unbalancing, why dont you get the ability and try it.   <P>posted December 12, 2001 03:23 AM                    <BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>List your reason(or comments) why Dire charm (needs to be)and will be nerfed,mine are:<BR>1.The refresh time is barelly over 1 hr (real time)and the cost to attain this incredible skill is fairly easy to get (relativelly speaking). - it is 72 minutes you cannot use this ability if you try to charm a mob that is too high, or if you let your pet die.  i can cast allure within a few seconds of each other right now.  and as far as fairly easy to obtain, have you gotten it yet?<P>2.This will make us (enchanters)the best pet class (yes including epic mages)even though we are not a true pet class. An obvious design flaw. - and this isnt true now since we already have this ability because....?<P>3.This will radically change high lvl enchanter class by making us the best soloer in the game by a large margin(at least now we have some sort of competition). - ok you cant get this till level 59 so you wont be soloing for exp much with it, and why would this be better than charm soloing?  with charm soloing you get the exp for the mob you kill plus your pet.  with this your pet finishs low on health you have to wait for him to heal up.  less efficient.<P>4.This will unbalence some epic encounters (that VI cherish) so much and make them instead pushover mobs.They put in safeguards for tov/vp/sky ect but many zones are still available for the picking. - if you consider breaking chef in seb a epic encounter then i guess you are right, it will be helpful for this.<P>5.Nothing else,for any class,approaches being this good.(although duids/necros get the ghetto version) - have you even looked at some of the things other classes are getting?  alot of classes get nice upgrades with sol, this was our one saving grace but it is no better than alot of the other skills.<P>6.It will make the duo combination enchanter cleric silly powerful.The efficiency of CH on mob pets approaches the ridiculous,hasnt VI learned from AoW incident? - and this is different than charming using allure how?  where do you keep getting these low level pets that are going to destroy uber mobs at?<P>7.It will make many lewt that is designed specifically to be available for groups only, attainable by a solo enchanter.(VI really hate this)- and you are going to restate that enchanters can solo how many times in this top 10 list?<P>8.This tool will make power levelling incredibly powerfull - like we needed help in this area<P>9.Some enchanter will either unententionally or maliciously perma charm a PH for a named mob thus preventing his spawn on a permanent basis. - scary as it is this is a valid point.  verant can mark a mob as uncharmable, alot of quest ones already are, they might have to add this code to ph's. i think petitioning though would be enough to get it taken care of if an enchanter is being a nuisence in this way.<P>10. Finally,it's too good to be true, the classic sign of something that is game unbalancing. - this isnt a valid argument so i dont feel the need to dispute it.  i could say "its just not good enough, the classic sign it is underpowered".  this is an opinion, not an argument.
